assignments.value:
=Compare this job posting against this candidate's resume bullets.

JOB POSTING:
{{$json.body.jobPosting}}

RESUME BULLETS:
{{$json.body.resumeBullets}}

Return ONLY valid JSON, no markdown, no extra text, in this exact format:
{"matchPercentage": 72, "matchedSkills": ["skill or requirement that overlaps", "another one"], "missingSkills": ["requirement from the posting not covered by the resume"], "summary": "one short encouraging sentence about the overall fit"}

Keep each skill/requirement entry short (2-5 words). List at most 6 items per array, prioritizing the most important ones.

parameters.jsCode:
const response = $input.first().json;
const rawText = response.candidates[0].content.parts[0].text;
const cleaned = rawText.replace(/```json|```/g, '').trim();
const result = JSON.parse(cleaned);

return [{
  json: {
    matchPercentage: result.matchPercentage,
    matchedSkills: result.matchedSkills,
    missingSkills: result.missingSkills,
    summary: result.summary
  }
}];
